@startuml auto-recovery-flow
!include _standard-style.puml

title Auto-Recovery Flow & Plug'n'Play Behavior

participant "User Session" as User
participant "Health Prompt Hook" as HPH
participant "Global Process\nSupervisor (GPS)" as GPS
participant "Global LSL\nCoordinator" as GLC
participant "Enhanced Transcript\nMonitor" as ETM
participant "Health Files" as HF

== Normal Operation ==
User -> User : Start Claude session via `coding`
activate GLC
GLC -> ETM : Ensure transcript monitor for project
activate ETM
ETM -> HF : Write health data every 5 seconds
GLC -> GLC : Perform health check every 30 seconds
User -> User : Display [LSL🟢]

== Recovery 1: Dead Monitor (Coordinator Active) ==
ETM --> GLC : Process not found (kill -0 fails)
deactivate ETM
GLC -> GLC : Mark monitor as unhealthy
GLC -> ETM : Start new monitor process
activate ETM
ETM -> HF : Resume health file updates
note right : **GLC is primary supervisor**\nGPS detects GLC via pgrep → skips restart

== Recovery 2: Dead Monitor (No Coordinator) ==
note over GLC : Coordinator not running\n(session closed, no daemon)
deactivate GLC
GPS -> HF : Read health file timestamp
HF --> GPS : File age > 120 seconds
GPS -> ETM : Kill stale monitor
deactivate ETM
GPS -> ETM : Start fresh monitor
activate ETM
ETM -> HF : Write current health data
note right : **GPS as fallback supervisor**\nOnly acts when GLC is absent

== Recovery 3: GPS Budget Exhausted ==
note over GPS : 10 restarts/hour reached\nGPS gives up
HPH -> HF : Check LSL health (pre-prompt)
HF --> HPH : Status: stopped / stale
HPH -> HPH : Check lockfile age (>60s?)
HPH -> GLC : Spawn coordinator (fire-and-forget)
activate GLC
GLC -> ETM : Ensure transcript monitor
activate ETM
ETM -> HF : Resume health file updates
note right : **Prompt hook safety net**\nRate-limited to 1 attempt/minute

== Recovery 4: Idle Timeout Guard ==
note over ETM : No transcript activity for 30 minutes
ETM -> ETM : Check tmux pane cwd
ETM -> ETM : Active tmux session found
ETM -> ETM : Reset activity timer, stay alive
note right : **Prevents restart budget waste**\nMonitor stays alive while session exists

== Dynamic Session Discovery ==
User -> User : Start new project session
GLC -> GLC : Discover new project
GLC -> ETM : Start monitor for new project
activate ETM
note right : **Zero-config:** New sessions\nautomatically get monitoring

note over User, HF
  **Supervisor Priority Order:**

  |= Priority |= Supervisor |= When Active |
  | 1 | GlobalLSLCoordinator | Session running (launched by coding) |
  | 2 | GlobalProcessSupervisor | No coordinator → GPS manages monitors |
  | 3 | HealthPromptHook | GPS exhausted → spawns coordinator |

  **Key Prevention Mechanisms:**
  - GPS defers to GLC via pgrep check (no dual-supervisor conflict)
  - Monitor checks tmux cwd before idle-exit (no budget waste)
  - Prompt hook rate-limited via lockfile (no spawn storm)
end note

@enduml
